title: 24 hours in Oslo | 5 cool city walks

ai_json.title: 24 hours in Oslo | 5 cool city walks

properties.title: 24 Hours in Oslo
properties.description: Extracted itinerary from the Visit Norway guide to city walks in Oslo.

properties.name: Nordmarka, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A vast forested area north of Oslo popular for hiking, skiing, and outdoor recreation.

properties.name: Akerselva River, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A scenic river running through Oslo, lined with waterfalls, bridges, and cultural sites.

properties.name: Harbour Promenade, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A waterfront walking route connecting key attractions along Oslo’s modern harbor.

properties.name: Deichman Library, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: Oslo’s award-winning public library featuring innovative architecture and cultural spaces.

properties.name: MUNCH Museum, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A waterfront museum dedicated to artist Edvard Munch, home to The Scream and other masterpieces.

properties.name: Talormade Oslobukta, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A popular specialty donut and coffee shop located in Oslo’s Oslobukta district.

properties.name: Operastranda, Bjørvika, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A small urban beach in the Bjørvika district near the Oslo Opera House.

properties.name: Deichman Bjørvika, Oslo Public Library Main Branch, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: The main branch of Oslo’s public library system, known for modern design and cultural events.

properties.name: SALT, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A cultural venue combining saunas, food stalls, and outdoor stages with a Nordic aesthetic.

properties.name: Anker Bridge, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A pedestrian bridge crossing Akerselva, connecting neighborhoods around Grünerløkka.

properties.name: Mathallen Food Hall, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A large indoor food hall offering diverse eateries, local specialties, and artisan goods.

properties.name: The Palace Park, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A landscaped public park surrounding the Royal Palace in central Oslo.

properties.name: The Royal Palace, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: The official residence of the Norwegian monarch, located at the end of Karl Johans gate.

properties.name: Oslo City Hall, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A landmark civic building known for its Nordic architecture and Nobel Peace Prize ceremony.

properties.name: Akershus Fortress, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A medieval fortress overlooking Oslofjord, offering historic buildings and city views.

properties.name: Vippa Oslo, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A vibrant street-food hall on the waterfront featuring global cuisine and communal seating.

properties.name: Koie Ramen Munch, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A ramen restaurant located near the MUNCH museum; popular for Tokyo-style bowls.

properties.name: Bjørvika, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A modern waterfront district known for architecture, culture, and food spaces.

properties.name: The Tiger Sculpture, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A bronze tiger sculpture near Oslo Central Station symbolizing the city’s nickname, ‘Tigerstaden’.

properties.name: Åretak Viking Rowboat Rental, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A rental service offering Viking-style wooden rowboats for exploring Oslo’s waterfront.

properties.name: Sørenga, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A fjordfront neighborhood filled with eateries, swimming areas, and waterfront trails.

properties.name: Mirabel Sørenga, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A Mediterranean-inspired restaurant in Oslo’s Sørenga district.

properties.name: Sørenga Social Club, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A waterfront cocktail bar in Sørenga offering views of the fjord.

properties.name: Bun's Burger Bar Sørenga, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A casual burger restaurant located in Sørenga, popular with locals and visitors.

properties.name: Astrup Fearnley Museum, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A contemporary art museum on Tjuvholmen, designed by Renzo Piano.

properties.name: Fineart Oslo, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A major contemporary art gallery and exhibition space on the waterfront.

properties.name: Queen Sonja Art Stable, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A royal art space showcasing exhibitions in the former royal stables near the palace.

properties.name: Kunstnernes Hus, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A historic artist-run art institution hosting exhibitions, film, and cultural events.

properties.name: The House of Literature (Litteraturhuset), Oslo, Norway
properties.description: One of Europe’s largest literary houses offering debates, lectures, and cultural programming.

properties.name: Gallery Albin Upp, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A contemporary gallery in Oslo’s Briskeby area hosting exhibitions by Norwegian and international artists.

properties.name: The Vigeland Museum, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A museum dedicated to the works of Gustav Vigeland next to the world-famous sculpture park.

properties.name: Vigeland Sculpture Park, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A world-renowned sculpture park featuring over 200 works by Gustav Vigeland.

properties.name: Anne På Landet, Frogner Park, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A charming café located inside Frogner Park serving pastries, coffee, and small meals.

properties.name: Botanical Garden, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: Oslo’s botanical gardens featuring themed plant collections, greenhouses, and walking paths.

properties.name: Grünerløkka Brygghus, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A craft brewery and gastropub located in the vibrant Grünerløkka district.

properties.name: Velouria Vintage, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A curated vintage clothing store specializing in fashion from various eras.

properties.name: Haralds Vaffel, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A beloved waffle stand known for serving Norwegian-style waffles with creative toppings.

properties.name: Frøken Dianas Salonger, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A boutique offering vintage-inspired clothing, accessories, and design pieces.

properties.name: Ingensteds, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A popular nightlife venue on the banks of Akerselva featuring DJs, concerts, and cultural events.

properties.name: Blå, Oslo, Norway
properties.description: A legendary Oslo club known for live music, electronic nights, and an artistic riverside atmosphere.
